  "metadata": {
    "title": "CVE-2017-7895 kernel: NFSv3 server does not properly handle payload bounds checking of WRITE requests (important)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2017-7895",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2017-7895",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: The NFSv2 and NFSv3 server implementations in the Linux kernel through 4.10.13 lacked certain checks for the end of a buffer. A remote attacker could trigger a pointer-arithmetic error or possibly cause other unspecified impacts using crafted requests related to fs/nfsd/nfs3xdr.c and fs/nfsd/nfsxdr.c. \n            STATEMENT: This issue affects the versions of the Linux kernel as shipped with Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5, 6, 7 and Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2. Future kernel updates for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5, 6, 7 and Red Hat Enterprise MRG 2 may address this issue.",
